widgets_values: Segmenting the person and removing the head. Purpose is to use the image of the person  for generating Canny edges. Segmenting to get freedom over background. Removed head for freedom over face.

For refiner using softedge controlnet to fix boundary issues.

For the boundary problem here, Canny has hard edges so Canny controlnet here will also produce similar boundary issues.
Using higher controlnet strengths here leads to faded image. Try to keep the sum near 1.
This is used for artifact fix (refiner)
Use the same prompts as the main inputs or create a good generic prompt that adds details to all images.

Load 2k images; Both the image and the mask are downscaled by 1/2 for the inpainting.
Load Mask must be RGBA image, alpha values are considered as the mask.
Highres image and mask are passed to upscaler.

KSampler converts the mask to binary so doing it outside for more control based on threshold.
Added dilation to increase the area of inpainting. It will inpaint few pixels inside the garment so that there is no bleed when the garment is overlaid later.
Inverted to get garment mask as white pixels as they had alpha of 0 in PNG.
